Line Rules

Use <strong> and <em> instead of <b> and <i>

Hanging quote marks or bullets:
use negative text-indent or margins

HTML charactor entities 
for quotation mars and dashes
&ldquo; &rdquo;
&ndash; &mdash
&hellip; &amp;
impressivewebs.com 
dev.w3.com 

GRADIENTS
linear gradients 2 or more colors defined on linear line
radial gradients

background: -webkit-linear-gradient(orange, darkblue);
default runs from top to bottom. Can change where gradient should start and end
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(bottom, orange, darkblue);
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(bottom, right, orange, darkblue);
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(0deg, orange, darkblue); -define the angle where the gradient should start
Color stops:
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(orange, darkblue 50%, green 50%(or px length), purple);

New syntax for gradients:
background: linear-gradient(0deg, orange, darkblue, purple);
*Have to use several codes for this for browser compatibility

Radial Gradients
Start from the center
background: -webkit-radial-gradient(150px(or%) 50px(or%), closet-corner, #e3a112, darkblue);

Radial Gradients: Unprefixed syntax
<shape><size> at <position> color stops
background: radial-gradient(circle farthest-side at 30% 15%, aqua, darkblue);
*will need to include the prefixed syntax for older browsers

Transparent Gradients

Full background gradient:
html {
	height 100%
}
body {
	background: -webkit-linear-gradient(hsl(218, 51%, 32%), transparent, 75%);
}

overlay on image:
body {
	background: -webkit-linear-gradient(hsl(218, 51%, 32%), transparent, 75%), url('bg.lu');
	background-size: cover;
}
rgba(255,255,255,0) instead of transparent to get rid of grayish tone

Repeating Gradients
background: -webkit-repeating-linear-gradient(left rgba(58, 122, 187, .8), rgba(43, 79,115) 50px);
background: -webkit-repeating-radial-gradient(0 0, circle, rgba(108, 144, 188, .8), rgb(75, 113, 160) 20px, rgba(108, 144, 188, .8) 6px);
Gradient Generators:
colorzilla.com/gradient-editor

FLEXBOX
Chrome and Opera support flexbox

.nav {
	display: -webkit-flex;
	-webkit-flex-direction: row, row-reverse, column, column-reverse;
	-webkit-justify-content: space-between, flex-end, center;
	-web-kit-flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.nav li:first-child {
	margin-right: auto;
}

.nav li {
	-webkit-flex-grow: 1;
}

.col {
	-webkit-flex: 1;
}

.col c {
	-webkit-flex: 2;
	-webkit-order: -1;
}

.col-b {
	-webkit-align-self: center, flex-end, stretch;
}

@medi screen and (max-width: 999px) {
	.main {
		-webkit-flex-direction: column;
	}
}

modernizer.com - gives you alternatives for flexbox for older browsers

